        ("Disciplinary Core Idea", "ESS3.C Human Impacts on Earth Systems / ETS1.A Defining and Delimiting Engineering Problems", "Human development fundamentally alters the water cycle by replacing permeable surfaces with impervious ones. Engineering solutions must account for societal inequities and prioritize the most vulnerable populations."),
        ("Crosscutting Concept", "Cause and Effect", "Students trace the causal chain from historical policy decisions (redlining, disinvestment) through infrastructure disparities to unequal flood outcomes, identifying both proximate causes (impervious surfaces, old pipes) and root causes (systemic racism).")
