        {"num": "Slide 2", "title": "Learning Objectives", "visual": "Learning goals and vocabulary terms", "say": "Today we're modeling the physics of silence — how two waves that are each individually loud can combine to produce nothing. It's one of the most beautiful results in all of physics.", "do": "Have students read objectives. Pre-teach 'superposition' and 'destructive interference' with a visual animation of two waves combining.", "time": "3 min"},
