        {"num": "Slide 2", "title": "Learning Objectives", "visual": "Learning goals and vocabulary terms", "say": "Today we're modeling the mathematics of contagion — the same equations that epidemiologists use to predict, and try to prevent, the next pandemic.", "do": "Have students read objectives. Pre-teach R0 with the rice-on-a-chessboard analogy: if each grain doubles, how many squares until the board overflows? (Answer: 64 squares, final square has 9.2 quintillion grains.)", "time": "3 min"},
