        {"num": "Slide 4", "title": "LEVER Framework", "visual": "LEVER steps overview", "say": "We're building the same model the CDC and WHO use to predict outbreaks. It's called the SIR model, and it's surprisingly simple — just three boxes and two arrows.", "do": "Draw S → I → R on the board. Explain: people flow from Susceptible to Infected to Recovered. The speed of the first arrow is the whole game.", "time": "2 min"},
